"Futurama" is an animated sci-fi sitcom that follows the adventures of Philip J. Fry, a slacker who is accidentally frozen in a cryogenic chamber and wakes up 1,000 years later in the 31st century. He becomes part of a spacefaring crew that includes Leela, a tough one-eyed alien, and Bender, a robot with a bad attitude and a love for alcohol. Together, they work for the Planet Express delivery company, navigating through bizarre futuristic worlds and facing off against strange alien species, time paradoxes, and the occasional intergalactic villain. The series blends sharp humor, satirical social commentary, and heartwarming moments while exploring themes like technology, relationships, and the nature of humanity in a futuristic setting.

title: Bender Just Discovered NFTsâ€¦ #Futurama
description:
In Futurama Season 12, Episode 1, Bender dives headfirst into the NFT craze â€” dancing, posing, and minting ridiculous â€œBender Collectionâ€ tokens like â€œBender with Sombrero.â€

His plan? Buy one himself to trick the algorithm into making it look valuable. Soon, the "suckers" start buying in and it all takes offâ€¦ until itâ€™s time to count the profits.

Bender thinks heâ€™s made millions â€” turns out, he made $94. But in true Bender fashion, he still celebrates like he just scammed the planet. This is Futurama doing what it does best: clowning the future with style.

title: The Making of Futurama was a Sh*t Show (Pt 1: 1999-2003)
description:
Following up after The Simpsons is hard. Letâ€™s talk about how difficult it was to make Futurama, from Fox questioning every aspect of the show to dooming it with a terrible timeslot.

Watch Part 2 here: https://youtu.be/w5kwMoq8JyA

In the entertainment world, there are millions of dollars on the line and troubled productions are bound to happen. Whether it's big egos, bigger budgets, or just plain bad luck, we are going behind-the-scenes on these disastrous, never ending, and sometimes dangerous productions. From the creators of WTF Happened To This Movie?, It Was A Sh*t Show is a video essay/documentary/podcast series looking at some of your favorite films and tv shows, and why they were such a nightmare to make.

Fry, a pizza delivery guy who is accidentally cryogenically frozen on New Yearâ€™s Eve in 1999 and wakes up in the 31st century. He joins the interplanetary delivery company "Planet Express" and teams up with a one-eyed pilot named Leela, an alcoholic, sarcastic robot named Bender, and a quirky crew of characters. With its blend of science fiction, satire, and social commentary, Futurama has earned a loyal fanbase around the world.

title: "There's no doubt Bender holds a special place in Fry's heart."
description:
#Futurama #Futurama Movie #Futurama TV Show #Futurama Series #Bender #Fry #Leela #Amy Wong #Professor Farnsworth #Bender's Big Score #Zoidberg #Maggie #Matt Groening #Futurama Episodes #Futurama Characters #Futurama Cast #Futurama Plot #Bender the Robot #Fry the Human #Leela the Cyclops #Bender's Revenge #Futurama Season 1 #Futurama Season 4 #Futurama Season 7 #Futurama Futurama Movie #Futurama Comedy #Sci-Fi Animation #Futurama Humor #Futurama Space #Futurama Future #Futurama 2020 #Bender's Family #Futurama Alien #Futurama Time Travel #Futurama Robots #Futurama Comedy Series #Bender and Fry #Futurama Episodes Ranking #Amy and Kif #Leela and Fry #Futurama Quotes #Futurama Memes #Futurama Character Development #Leela and Fry Relationship #Futurama Space Adventures #Futurama Humor Series #Bender's Quotes #Futurama Sci-Fi Themes #Futurama Timeline #Futurama Robots and Humans #Futurama Space Exploration
Futurama is a science fiction animated sitcom created by Matt Groening, set in the 31st century. The series follows the adventures of Philip J. Fry, a slacker who is accidentally frozen in a cryogenic chamber and wakes up 1,000 years later in the future. After his awakening, Fry starts working at the Planet Express delivery company, which is run by the eccentric and elderly Professor Farnsworth.
Fry's new coworkers include the tough but lovable Leela, a one-eyed mutant, and the often misbehaving robot Bender. Together, they embark on various bizarre and humorous adventures across space, dealing with aliens, robots, time travel, and the ups and downs of life in the future. Throughout the series, Fry also tries to adjust to his new life in the future, navigating his relationship with Leela and uncovering the mysteries of his past.
The show combines witty humor, satirical takes on modern society, and thoughtful explorations of technology, love, and friendship, making it a beloved classic among fans of animated science fiction.

Futurama is a science fiction animated sitcom created by Matt Groening, set in the 31st century. The series follows the adventures of Philip J. Fry, a slacker who is accidentally frozen in a cryogenic chamber and wakes up 1,000 years later in the future. After his awakening, Fry starts working at the Planet Express delivery company, which is run by the eccentric and elderly Professor Farnsworth.
Fry's new coworkers include the tough but lovable Leela, a one-eyed mutant, and the often misbehaving robot Bender. Together, they embark on various bizarre and humorous adventures across space, dealing with aliens, robots, time travel, and the ups and downs of life in the future. Throughout the series, Fry also tries to adjust to his new life in the future, navigating his relationship with Leela and uncovering the mysteries of his past.
The show combines witty humor, satirical takes on modern society, and thoughtful explorations of technology, love, and friendship, making it a beloved classic among fans of animated science fiction.

"Futurama" is an animated sci-fi sitcom that follows the adventures of Philip J. Fry, a slacker who is accidentally frozen in a cryogenic chamber and wakes up 1,000 years later in the 31st century. He becomes part of a spacefaring crew that includes Leela, a tough one-eyed alien, and Bender, a robot with a bad attitude and a love for alcohol. Together, they work for the Planet Express delivery company, navigating through bizarre futuristic worlds and facing off against strange alien species, time paradoxes, and the occasional intergalactic villain. The series blends sharp humor, satirical social commentary, and heartwarming moments while exploring themes like technology, relationships, and the nature of humanity in a futuristic setting.
